atar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/klaus/{size}/271372_2.png","created_at":"2025-04-17T05:00:04.147Z","cooked":"<p>Hi<br>
We analise via robot pose, which coral station is the closest to the robot, after that, we set the target angle for the swerve.<br>
Here is the code for this detection:</p>
<pre><code class="lang-auto">private Pose2d getNearestCoralStationPose() {
    if (DriverStation.getAlliance().get() == Alliance.Red) {
      if (this.getPose().getY() &gt;= FieldConstants.CenterY) {
        return SwerveConstants.CoralStations.RedAliance.CORAL_STATION_RIGHT_POSE_FOR_ROBOT;
      } else {
        return SwerveConstants.CoralStations.RedAliance.CORAL_STATION_LEFT_POSE_FOR_ROBOT;
      }
    } else {
      if (this.getPose().getY() &gt;= FieldConstants.CenterY) {
        return SwerveConstants.CoralStations.BlueAliance.CORAL_STATION_LEFT_POSE_FOR_ROBOT;
      } else {
        return SwerveConstants.CoralStations.BlueAliance.CORAL_STATION_RIGHT_POSE_FOR_ROBOT;
      }
    }
  }

</code></pre>
